				<div id="left-sbm-top">
					<h1>Expert Blog</h1>  
															        
					<div class="view view-blog-post view-id-blog_post view-display-id-page_1 view-dom-id-1">
        <div class="view-header">
      <p><em>ChinaFAQs experts react to the latest headlines about China climate and energy issues.</em></p>
    </div>
  
  
  
      <div class="view-content">
        <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Cancun.jpg" alt="" title="" width="180" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../report-cancun-china-emphasizes-energy-policy-progress">Report from Cancun:  China Emphasizes Energy Policy Progress</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">December 05, 2010</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>As the first week of negotiations in Cancun concludes, China has been stressing its progress at home.  That China takes the climate change issue seriously was the principal message at a recent Cancun event from Su Wei, the Director-General of China‚Äôs Climate Change Department under its powerful National Development and Reform Commission (NDRC) and lead climate negotiator.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../report-cancun-china-emphasizes-energy-policy-progress">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/energy-and-emissions-data">Energy and Emissions Data</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/renewables-and-alternative-energy">Renewables and Alternative Energy</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/iStock_000008580451Small_1.jpg" alt="" title="" width="180" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../report-cancun-chinas-climate-progress-copenhagen">Report from Cancun:  China‚Äôs Climate Progress Since Copenhagen</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">November 30, 2010</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>As negotiators arrive in Cancun for the next round of global climate talks, speculation once again hovers around China‚Äôs positions.  China is a tough negotiator, and we can once again see it expressing concern about its core issues, including developed country mitigation commitments, technology transfer and the adequacy of financing.  But as we look to negotiating positions, it is also worth stepping back for a minute to reflect on what China is doing domestically and how China‚Äôs efforts to promote energy efficiency and low carbon technologies can contribute to the global effort to combat climate change.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../report-cancun-chinas-climate-progress-copenhagen">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/energy-efficiency">Energy Efficiency</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/policy-and-governance">Policy and Governance</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/renewables-and-alternative-energy">Renewables and Alternative Energy</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/transportation">Transportation</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-3 views-row-odd">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/students_1_11-30-10.JPG" alt="" title="" width="160" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../students-us-and-china-collaborate-mou-be-presented-cop-16">Students from the U.S. and China Collaborate on MOU to be Presented at COP-16</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Angel Hsu</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">November 30, 2010</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p><em>‚ÄúLate last year, Ren and around 40 other young Chinese people arrived in Copenhagen, hoping to break the silence of their peers on the international issue of climate change. They constituted the largest Chinese youth group ever to take part in a United Nations climate-change summit.‚Äù</p>

<p>-China Dialogue, April 14, 2010</em></p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
